Percy Sutton, a prominent figure in the African American community, has passed away. He was known for his service as a Tuskegee Airman, state assemblyman, Manhattan Borough President, and for his efforts to revitalize the Apollo Theater in Harlem. His dedication to civil rights and his career as an entrepreneur and public servant paved the way for many young African Americans. The President and First Lady express their condolences to his family during this difficult time.